  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict hemolysis in centrifugal blood pump configurations. The CFD hemolysis model targets the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device operating conditions. All thirteen ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been evaluated; seven factors were fully assessed and six were partially assessed with documented epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across the operating envelope. The assessment team determined that the achieved credibility levels are sufficient for the intended engineering decision, and the package is submitted under the Minimal profile which does not mandate a structured Context of Use block.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-credibility-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-velocity-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-monte-carlo-uq-samples"
  ],
