      "name": "Pressure-head curve validation across flow range"
    }
  ],
  "wasDerivedFrom": "https://doi.org/10.1115/1.4042689",
  "wasAttributedTo": "https://uofa.net/synth/org/morrison-biofluid-simulation-group",
  "generatedAtTime": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z",
  "hash": "sha256:a3f1c2e4b7d09812fe563a1c4b8d2e7f3a91c05b6d4e2f8a1c3b7d9e0f2a4c6",
  "signature": "ed25519:b2c4d6e8f0a1b3c5d7e9f1a2b4c6d8e0f2a4b6c8d0e2f4a6b8c0d2e4f6a8b0",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented test suite covering all active physics modules; independent code review completed.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver is under version control and a regression test suite exists covering core fluid dynamics modules. However, the hemolysis damage model sub-routine has not been independently reviewed, and test coverage for the power-law RBC damage integral is incomplete. Achieved level 3 falls below the required level 4 for MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests demonstrated for all governing equations; manufactured solution verification completed for hemolysis transport.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy testing was performed for the Navier-Stokes solver and confirmed second-order spatial convergence. Manufactured solution verification for the scalar hemolysis transport equation was initiated but not completed for all boundary condition types. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for hemolysis index QoI on at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI below 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels were generated with a refinement ratio of 1.3. Richardson extrapolation yielded a GCI of 8.2% for the normalized index of hemolysis, exceeding the 5% threshold. The near-wall resolution in the volute tongue region remains a source of elevated discretization error. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions documented with uncertainty bounds; inlet velocity profiles and fluid rheology matched to simulation inputs.",
      "rationale": "The FDA benchmark experimental data provides flow rate and pressure-head measurements with stated uncertainties. However, inlet velocity profile characterization is limited to bulk flow rate; spatially resolved inlet profiles were not measured. Blood analogue rheology was characterized at a single shear rate. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative validation metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty) computed for hemolysis index; statistical comparison accounts for experimental and numerical uncertainties.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis predicted by CFD differs from experimental measurements by 34% at the design point and up to 61% at off-design conditions. Validation uncertainty was estimated via Monte Carlo but the model form error dominates. The comparison metric does not meet the acceptance threshold. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to clinical hemolysis endpoints; linkage between NIH and device performance specification documented.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis is a recognized surrogate for in-vivo hemolysis but the quantitative linkage to plasma free hemoglobin thresholds relevant to VAD clinical performance has not been formally documented in this assessment. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments cover the full operating envelope of the VAD COU including flow rate range, rotational speed range, and hematocrit range.",
      "rationale": "Validation data from the FDA benchmark covers the nominal operating point and two off-design flow rates. The rotational speed range tested (2500 RPM only) does not span the full VAD operating envelope (2000–3500 RPM). Hematocrit was fixed at 40%; clinical variability was not explored experimentally. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated to machine precision for all QoIs; round-off error analysis documented.",
      "rationale": "Iterative residuals were monitored and dropped six orders of magnitude for momentum equations; however, the hemolysis scalar transport equation residuals plateaued at four orders of magnitude reduction. Round-off error analysis was not performed. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented user qualification requirements; simulation execution checklist; independent review of simulation setup by a second analyst.",
      "rationale": "No formal user qualification procedure or simulation execution checklist exists for this model. Independent review of mesh generation and boundary condition setup was not performed. This factor represents a significant epistemic gap for MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic model form uncertainty quantification; comparison of multiple turbulence and hemolysis damage model formulations with documented selection rationale.",
      "rationale": "The power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model was selected without systematic comparison to alternative damage models (e.g., Arora, Taskin). Turbulence model sensitivity was assessed only between k-omega SST and k-epsilon, without wall-resolved LES comparison. Model form uncertainty is a dominant source of prediction error. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterized with probability distributions; global sensitivity analysis identifies dominant inputs; distributions propagated via Monte Carlo.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed propagating distributions for viscosity, density, hemolysis model coefficients (C, alpha, beta), and rotational speed. Global sensitivity analysis via Sobol indices identified the hemolysis model exponent alpha as the dominant input. However, geometric manufacturing tolerances were not included in the uncertainty propagation. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental hemolysis measurements from multiple pump specimens; inter-specimen variability quantified; sample size sufficient for statistical comparison.",
      "rationale": "The FDA benchmark hemolysis data derives from a single pump specimen tested in one laboratory. Inter-specimen variability and inter-laboratory reproducibility are not characterized. The single-sample experimental basis is insufficient for MRL 5 statistical comparison requirements. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal mapping documented between validation experiment input parameters and COU input parameters; differences quantified and their impact on QoI assessed.",
      "rationale": "The validation experiments use a blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water mixture) rather than human blood. The viscosity and density are matched at the design point but the non-Newtonian shear-thinning behavior of blood at low shear rates is not captured by the analogue. No formal assessment of the impact of this fluid equivalency gap on hemolysis prediction has been performed. Achieved level 2."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-hemolysis-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Although multiple credibility factors achieved levels below their required thresholds and six factors carry documented epistemic gaps, the assessment team determined that the aggregate evidence is sufficient to support the engineering decision within the scope of this clinical research application. The Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification provides bounded predictions, and the dominant uncertainty sources (model form, test samples) have been identified and will be addressed in the next assessment cycle. The package is submitted under the Minimal profile; a structured Context of Use has not been formally encoded, as the intended-use scope is described narratively in the package description. The decision is Accepted with the understanding that the gaps identified herein must be resolved prior to any regulatory submission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
